Guido engine and JNI for android : 

Run ndk-build and you're good to go.

This makefile build guido engine for android and build the native part for jni bridge.
The two of them are in the generated target GUIDOEngine-android.so.

You can change android ndk version to match your minSdk device target else ndk-build take the minimum ndk version install on your computer.
Default to android-16 (android version 4.1)

After that you can use this library in your android application, and use jni with the guidoengine-android.jar.
